<h1 id="security">Security</h1>
<p>Bottom line: If someone tells you Chocolatey <strong><em>is</em></strong> insecure, please respond with &quot;You mean Chocolatey <strong><em>used</em></strong> to be insecure. You may want to check out chocolatey dot org slash security and catch up with the last 2+ years. Or do you mean a <strong><em>community package</em></strong> may not be secure? Organizations typically do not use the community repository anyway and only use Chocolatey in a completely secure manner. Individuals looking for more protection with the community repository go Pro.&quot; (Some of the paid security features have significant recurring costs based on usage, so they can&#39;t be offered for free).</p>
